Risks and challenges
Probably the value we are asking for seems excessive, nevertheless, if you break it down, it's not: 

1 - To hire a professional sculptor; 
2 - To do the 3D modelling;
3 - Engineering and developing a sustainable biodegradable paste to build the structure based on shellfish;
4 - Quite a lot of tons of shrimp;
5 - Assembling a team of twenty or more people to build the actual structure;
6 - Urban licensing (which will be ridiculously expensive);
7 - Clean up costs;
8 - Inauguration event / Catering;
9 - Film and Photography;
10 - PR & Communication;
11 - Wires & Scaffolding.
12 - Sending out our rewards all over the world.

Any questions, doubts, suggestions, animal rights activists, please feel free to let us know and we'll be happy to answer you all asap:
